XML.Hansard-Body-Small-Font-Hanging-Indent2:
‘(1H)	If a person is convicted of a drink-driving offence committed after the commencement of this section (the 
current conviction
) and the court before whom the person is convicted is satisfied that, at the material time, the person was over the high alcohol limit and the person, within the period of 5 years before the current conviction, has been previously convicted more than once of a drink-driving offence involving a finding that, at the material time, the person was over the high alcohol limit, the person is disqualified absolutely by the current conviction and without any specific order from the date of the current conviction from holding or obtaining a Queensland driver licence.’.’.
